value.title: DOJ inspector general launches review of Trump-era seizure of members of Congress' communications
value.excerpt: Department of Justice Inspector General Michael Horowitz announced Friday that his office had initiated a review of the DOJ’s use of subpoenas and other legal authorities to obtain communication records of Members of Congress and of some in the news media.
